what. what the hell is this?

took only a few times to get my damn password right

Yeh, so the last time I updated this thing was at least two months ago saying that I only had three more days left till heading back to Clarion. Now it is five days till heading back to Clarion, till only having 2 1/2 more weeks till another break, and then 3 1/2-4 weeks before summer break. WTF
First day of classes and already it seems like a mixxed blessing...

three or four days left till I head back up to Clarion, -

three or four days till I am stuck back in Clarion, -

three or four days till I get to see everyone again +

Macbeth is over : (

It was a fun time when it lasted. I will remember it forever.  Afterwards we had Strike, it really didn't take all that long, which was a good thing.  Cast Party afterwards, always a good thing. By the time I got home and passed out I only had four hours of sleep before I had to be at the boyd to help move the seats back to where they were supposed to be.

I am now a brother of Alpha Psi Omega! Woot, one for my Major!

Two more days of classes, then Thanksgiving Break!

Last night of Macbeth,
I really don't know what to think about it, I really don't.
Mom, Steve and Katelyn are coming up from New Holland. And Dad, Jennie, and Terri are coming up as well.  It is going to be a huge family get together if they do not kill each other, that is.

THREE MORE DAYS!!!
Than I am HOME HOME!
Woot!
<font size="4">First day was great for Macbeth, hope the rest will be even better</font>

Macbeth

Macbeth

Tuesday Nov 14-18th, opens at 7:30pm, come
See IT!

Sup livejournal? How are you? How have you been? I don't really remember the last time I updated this thing, oh well.
Band is driving me nuts! I love and hate it at the same, how the hell does that work, I do not know. The show is good, the people are cool-for the most part, but yeah. It is just unfair some of the things that get done. If you let one person or group do something, let EVERYONE do it. Also, don't break up parts if you want to hear them, there is this thing called time delay-it sounds bad. Other than those two things, it is alright.
Theatre~Macbeth I forot about rehearsals on the stage side. Is that bad? It has been since 2003 that I was on stage stage for a major production. So this is interesting, fun, but interesting and amusing.
TBSPMA-yeah. Haven't really been to anything for two weeks because of rehearsal-so I have just about know clue what is really going on with any of it.

what is having a life?

theatre and band own my life, BLAH!
<font size="3">I just need to get out of clarion, I need to escape this place</font>

To much

To much

To much

...school work, band, theatre,Tbs, Pma all of thee above!

I mean I love doing everything, but at the same time I am looking at my schedule and going how the hell am I going to do all of this stuff? Then I have another frat. that I am doing/ hoping to do because it is in my major, then not to mention trying to do that Mary Walters thing on Wednesdays. Urgh. Then today in my Play directing class I find out that I have to, this week, meet with 4 groups and practice. So on top of everything, I have 3 on Wednesday after band( Starting at 6:30 because of me) and going till around 8, then Thursday I have one at 6 : ( then I have the one I am directing on Friday at 3 before band.  Top it off with not being able to go to one that I am in on Monday because of that festival thingy. I don't even know if this stuff makes any sense to anyone...

At times like this I am actually happy that I do not have a car, because right now I would be driving to god knows where.  I mean, I can time manage..but there is a limit for each person- and I think I am pushing it to my max( if I haven't broken it already) Hopefully I did not.

Song at 9, then back here to do more f-ing homework...
<font size="3">first home football game was saturday, GO BAND!</font>

for the first time since being here I am excited for the weekend, the first time this semester.  First homegame/first game we perform for for the season.  Should be interesting.  I forgot how good I am at B.S.ing music on the field, haha.  I know it isn't good, but at the same time it isn't bad.

Bowling with Phi Mu Alpha tonight, it was fun, 104, 92, 103.  Yeah, I suck at bowling, oh well it was fun none the less.

and an another and another and an another

I am tired

I want to sleep, but I can not

German = death

I need a day to sleep I believe, and not wake up at 7 am.  My body hates me I believe, I wake up at 7-7:30am every freaking day: EVERY DAY!!! It then takes me another 10-15 minutes to fall BACK asleep just to wake up at 8:30am or 9:30am.

First home football game this week....ewh, should be fun, I guess...

It is Wednesday
I should be happy that the week is almost over, but no.  I have so much stuff to do that it doesn't matter what day it is, I am still going nuts with trying to keep up with everything.
<font size="3">Coca~Cola Blak Taste and smells like SMORES!!!</font>

HOCKEY PRE~SEASON!!!!!!!!!

9 Days till the Flyers Vs. Penguins Game!

Woot!



I Like Hockey, unlike Football

This past week has been very clarion like, as in-odd.  It is odd to explain to people who do not go to college here, but they know how that is.  I am already getting annoyed with people here and it is only the third week, well fourth if I count marching band; which I wont because, I have more fun in marching band camp than I do in actually college...which is sad...but somewhat true.

Classes so far are, ewh, ok.  My Tuesday/Thursday classes are going to eat my soul.  Now, starting this week on Tuesdays I am going to be going from 9:30am (wake up at 8:30am) to 10pm, it is going to suck ass! I have three classes 9:30am to 1:45pm, break till 3:30, class till 5pm, meeting at 6:30pm, Sectionals at 7pm, and then Song at 9pm. So I have about 3 hours spread out on Tuesday to attempt to relax; attempt is the word there, ATTEMPT!! 

This is going to be a testing semester for me, and I do not think that I am yet ready for it.  Last week was TBSigma stuff, and now tomorrow starts the week for PhiMuAlpha stuff, untop of all of my work as is, URGH. But what can you do?

Plus...

I got casted into MacBeth! Happy me. But now I have to add that untop of my already huge ass pile of stuff that I have to do for classes, band, tbs/pma, and theatre itself, don't be shocked if you see me going nuts in the next month.
<font size="3">I had almost forgotten how much I do not like football</font>

long meeting


I want to drink


the router came today!!!!!

well one weekend almost down for this semester...blah
just about 90% of Clarion's population left this weekend to go home; which then in turn makes Clarion even more dead then it is any other day... it hurts, it really does.

I am bored out of my mind, go figure-right? I can't even remember what the hell I did on Friday other than going to see the DaVinci Code with Becky and Steve- and took about 100 pictures for my scene painting class

Saturday I did laundry with Theresa, Steve and JamieBebee and than watched Gramma's Boy- that is a great movie. Then didn't do much of anything until 8pm when I went over to Katie's and MattLoves.

Today, sunday-did NOTHING! So fucking bored
you know, Clarion sucks even more when about 90% of its population leaves for the weekend and you are stuck there, in Clarion

auditions blow!

I have no clue how I did...at all

it looks as if we have to get a new router for the computers, dammit!
it never takes long for the damn internet at where I live at to die!!!

first day of actual classes was today, woohoo
it already seems like it is going to be very different from last year, which I guess is a good thing more or less. 

This past week, sunday the 20th- saturday the 26th, was band camp. It was fun, my section rocks! But, it did take a total on my body thou.  Waking up at 6:50am and then not going to bed until anywhere from 12am-2am didn't do wonders for my body; but I loved every minute of it.

Classes for me today were alright, my first one being at 11am, second one at 12pm, and then band at 4pm.  Not that bad of a day, then tonight I had a Phi Mu Alpha meeting-and then Wednesday,as of now, I have a Tau Beta Sigma meeting at 8:30.  Tuesday/Thursday classes are going to be fun! Or not. My first class is at 9:30am, second at 11am, third at 12:30pm, fourth at 3:30, then sectionals at 7pm, and last song rehearsal at 9pm(Last two only on tuesdays) fun..fun..fun..

This coming Wednesday is going to stress me out, it had better be a good day at band. I have auditions that day, and then the meeting, urgh.  You know, I wouldn't be this stressed out if I didn't have to sing.  A month ago we were told that we only had to try out for either MacBeth, or The ThreePenny Opera-or both if you wanted to. No No No.  Now, last week, I believe Tuesday or Wednesday when I could finally get into the damn theatre department(Man. was waxing everythin) I found out that I have to do both, try out for both of them. URGH.  I really suck at the whole singing thing, I really do.  So, Wednesday is going to be fun.
<font size="3">wow, band camp is over, it went fast; I think I am going to miss it. ha. I am. I love it, as much as I bitch about it, I do love it.</font>

And back again

In fun old Clarion for the semester

band starts tomorrow-for a week, urgh

I've been at my mom's place in New Holland since Friday, it is Wednesday now- I want to leave.  It is worse than being in Hollidaysburg because I don't know anyone here-at all really, and have no means of going anywhere on my own.  I am leaving today at 5pm, and it can not come soon enough.  It is going to be a hell of a day, packing, and then having to drive two hours to meet my sister, and then traveling another two hours to get home to Hollidaysburg, urgh.  The only thing I want now is for me to be there.  I want to do something tonight with my friends at home, I think that is what is really getting me; I've worked all f-ing summer, third shift, so I haven't seen anyone really this summer- as much as I would like to anyway. 
 Tomorrow I head down to Gettysburg for the day with my dad.  I'm not really sure way I am going, I was the one who suggested it, but I am just the same.  It is going to be hot and packed with people as always-but what can you do...
 Friday I head back up to Clarion, most likely till November(grr), for freaking band camp- why I put myself thou all of this (band) I do not know.  Band for a week, and then classes start, whoo freaking whoo...
 It will be nice to see everyone from Clarion again...
 
 
 I need a car

done with the fucking factory, WOOT!
actually, Friday was supposed to be my last day, but... on monday the one fat bitch manager flipped out on me because I had one or two extra boxes ( which I was told I need four more) she tells me to count the envelopes and boxes and then told me to look at how many I was supposed to have; which then she followed with "You went to college didn't you?" in a smart ass sort of way- I turned and glared at her turned away then she muttered something in the line of "It was a waste of time" That fucking bitch, if I wasn't afraid of a lawsuit I would have punched the bitch.  The best thing is is that she has done this to many people- why the hell she is still there I do not know.

anywho, that is my rant on that

15 MORE DAYS LEFT!!!


Today was one of those " I want to leave now/fuck you" type of days at work...
so now that it feels as if my left wrist is going to fall off... F

it is now the part of the summer when things come to a stop for me and all I want is for college to start up again.
I want this whole loan consolidation thing to be done and over with, I want my loans and everything else to come in and to be shown on the damn website. 

I want a new job, or at least 1st fucking shift-the pay is the highest I've ever had, but now I have no life-and still no car. Speaking of that; it now seems it will be even longer till I get one. After looking around the area, with the money that I will be able to make during Thanksgiving, winter, and summer I might have enough money for a somewhat ok car and maybe a month or two worth for insurance. So, I figure I'll pay off the one bill I have left-that I know about, I better not have any fucking more-and then my credit will start to get better again so I can hope for a loan or just monthly payments on/for a newer car.

I've been thinking about the apartment up in Clarion a lot lately. I don't know if I like this whole living with Bryce's brother thing. It might be different if I had ever ment the guy. but I haven't.  If he is anything like Bryce, I don't know how much I will be able to deal.  Then again I only ever really hung out with him at parties, so that judgement is already off- it just feels like I am living in the fucking dorms again freshman year with a person I don't know.  But, I guess it is better than living with a person that the landlord would pick.  It is going to be interesting.  I just hope the damn internet works and that we don't kill each other in month.

Laundry is going to suck ass this year, having to pay for it again.  I hate it, plus having to wait for someone to drive me to the laundry mat seeing I still don't have a car.

I am hoping for less drama this year, if that is possible while living in the Boyd...
<font size="4">I HATE WAITING for all of the finanical aid stuff to come!</font>
oh livejournal land- how I don't update you anymore :/

So NOW the fucking bad neighbors son is driving so NOW they are parking all THREE of their FUCKING CARS (jeep wangler, jeep cher, and a pontiac) IN THE FRONT! The good/cool neighbor has one car; we have two. However! Terri parks her car infront of yard, not a house. We also have the "Third Child" a 2005 Chevy Silverodo which is about 20 plus feet long or something. I CAN NOT PULL INTO A FUCKING SPACE THAT I ONLY HAVE THREE FEET LEFT IN FRONT OR BEHIND ME!!!

THE FUCKS!!!
